      <h2>Our <span class="teal">Story</span></h2>
      <p class="content">The Unpaid CEO was born from a personal struggle. After years in corporate marketing, founder Amanda Johnson found herself juggling a demanding career with the needs of her young family. Despite her professional success, she felt like she was failing at both.</p>
      <p class="content">She realized that many women face the same challenge: they're expected to be the CEO of their households—managing schedules, finances, childcare, and more—all while pursuing their own career ambitions. Yet this vital role goes unrecognized and unpaid.</p>
      <p class="content">In 2020, she launched The Unpaid CEO as a blog to share her experiences. It quickly grew into a community of women supporting each other through the complex dance of career and family life. Today, we offer resources, community, and inspiration for women who refuse to choose between their ambitions and their families.</p>
</section>
